               <head>Muḥammad ‘Alī Ṭabāṭabā’ī Iṣfahānī's Rāḥat al-insān</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Rāḥat al-insān by Muḥammad ʿAlī Ṭabāṭabāʾī Iṣfahānī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010100939 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008111185" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16178-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A treatise on simple and compound remedies. By Muḥammad ʿAlī Ṭabāṭabāʾī Iṣfahānī (ca. 11th/17th century).</p>
                        <p>See Munzavī, FNKhF I p. 543, records only one other copy (Tehran University, Faculty of Medicine MS. 114/1). The present manuscript contains marginalia that include corrections as well as annotations, and so was presumably checked against another.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from A. Kazzaz.  </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22110">Rāḥat al-insān</title>
